The TNSP shall state the voltage at which a user may be connected following discussions and
considering the following factors:
(a) the user’s capacity or projected requirement and nature of the load to be connected;
(b) the present loading of the network;
(c) quality and security of supply considerations; and
(d) the plans for IPS development;

(a) the source impedance under maximum capacity conditions for each point of connection;
and
(b) the source impedance under minimum capacity conditions for each point of connection.

